title: South Africa beat New Zealand to win back-to-back Rugby World Cups
description: South Africa have made it back-to-back Rugby World Cup wins with victory over New Zealand.

title: 'There is no life': Anxious wait at Tel Aviv vigil as families worry if they will see family members again
description: In full sight of Israel's Ministry of Defence, whose responsibility it is to get the hostages back safely, a permanent vigil is held on a plaza in Tel Aviv.

title: Ongoing ground operation in Gaza is 'only the beginning' of next phase of war, Israel's PM says
description: Israel's Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has said the ongoing ground operation in Gaza is the "second stage of the war" after additional forces entered the territory.

title: South Korea party district mourns one year after 159 killed in Halloween crowd crush
description: The South Korean capital's nightlife district fell quiet on Saturday as hundreds mourned for the 159 people killed during a Halloween crowd crush one year ago.

title: Israel's latest ground raid into Gaza is different from what we've seen before
description: The latest ground raid into Gaza by Israeli troops has an important distinction from previous incursions. This time the soldiers did not immediately pull out after their attack.

title: Crash in Egypt kills 28 and injures 60
description: A multi-vehicle crash in Egypt has left 28 people dead and 60 others wounded, state media in the country have reported.

title: 'We can't even check on our families': Life inside Gaza after phone and internet lines cut
description: Gaza has been left largely isolated off from the outside world after Israel cut communications lines to the territory on Friday night.

title: Teenage girl allegedly attacked by Iranian morality police for not wearing headscarf dies
description: A teenage girl who was allegedly attacked by Iranian morality police for not wearing a headscarf has died, state media has said.

title: At least 21 dead in mine fire
description: At least 21 people have died in a fire at the largest steel mine in Kazakhstan.
